default2.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDecline in mail volumes is well documented. In 2010, the updated review
default of the postal services sector carried out by Richard Hooper for the Department for Business, Innovati
defaulton 
defaultand Skills noted that in 2005 the average Royal Mail daily mail bag contained 84 million addressed letters, packets and parcels but that by 2010 this was down to 71 million items. The following year, OFCOM identified that 
defaultthe UK postal sector had seen the steepest decline in volumes of any 
defaultEuropean country, falling by 25% since 2006, with Royal Mail volumes now approximately 62 million items per day
default.
default The updated review by Richard Hooper also notes that 
default‘Royal Mail predicts
default a further decline in Royal Mail addressed inland letter traffic volumes of over 20% between 2010/11 and 2015/16’
default.
default Royal Mail’
defaults 
