default2.10
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe capability, capacity and drive to innovate are critical components for any market 
defaultplayer looking to offer a consumer-focussed postal service. Retaining postal communication and delivery as a credible choice in an increasingly digital world also requires the availability of value-for-money, affordable products and services which meet the
default needs and demands of consumers and business customers.  
default&#xa0;
default2.11
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOur research report, Sense and Sustainability
default, interrogated residential and SME consumers’ needs from the postal service over the medium-term. We found that residential consumers expect greater innovation in terms of the delivery options for packets and parcels, including extending the number of pick
default up points, longer opening hours and more convenient locations – including pre-specified locations such as pubs or corner shops. SME consumers would like to see a range of delivery options offered, as is currently the case with all major courier companies,
default such as timed deliveries. 
default&#xa0;
default2.12
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt will be incumbent upon Royal Mail to be able to respond to these challenges in order to continue to fulfil its role as the designated universal service provider. It will need to offer innovative, cost-effective products and 
defaultdelivery solutions and maintain a dynamic approach 
defaultto a changing market and evolving consumer needs. Failure to adapt and respond to these challenges could have an adverse impact on the sustainability of the universal postal service and the ability of Roya
defaultl Mail to deliver that service.
